1.title: Buzzcuts & Beginnings
1.plot: The gang shares an emotional reunion in Miami at Ally's triumphant homecoming gig. When Austin learns that the foursome's time together is only temporary, he contemplates enrolling in military school.

2.title: Mattress Stores & Music Factories
2.plot: Unable to find a new passion, Austin feels forced to take a job at his parents' mattress store, and Ally struggles to keep up with an influx of music students.

3.title: Grand Openings & Great Expectations
3.plot: The gang has less than a week to teach first-time music students how to play in a band in anticipation of the A&A Music Factory's grand opening.

4.title: Seniors and Señors
4.plot: The foursome's plans to enjoy their senior year together are put on hold when Austin learns that he's a credit short and has to retake a Spanish test. Meanwhile, Ally freaks out when she is partnered with Dez in chemistry class.

5.title: Homework & Hidden Talents
5.plot: Austin, Ally, Trish, and Dez encounter a very talented student who is always out-shined by her sister always, so they must help her embrace her talent.

6.title: Duos & Deception
6.plot: Trish books Billie and Bobbie of "The Billie and Bobbie Show," a famous brother and sister duo, to talk and perform with the students of the A&A Music Factory. But later on, the foursome learns the famous duo have ulterior motives.

7.title: Wedding Bells & Wacky Birds
7.plot: When Austin and Ally are paired together in Home Economy, they get to imagine life together as a married couple. Trish helps Dez book a job directing a commercial.

8.title: Karaoke & Kalamity
8.plot: Desperate to perform again, Austin begins singing at a karaoke club in disguise. Back at the A&A Music Factory, Ally mentors a student with stage fright.

9.title: Mini-Me's & Muffin Baskets
9.plot: The gang prepares for the A&A Music Factory's first showcase and Austin wants to surprise Ally by teaching their students one of her songs.

10.title: Dancers & Ditzes
10.plot: Ally is set to perform at an awards show, but the producers are concerned over her limited dancing skills.

11.title: Mysteries & Meddling Kids
11.plot: A mystery unfurls when Ally's songbook is stolen from the school's '70s-themed party. The gang goes in search of the culprit.

12.title: Comebacks & Crystal Balls
12.plot: A visit with a fortune teller convinces Austin that something bad will happen during his comeback concert. Meanwhile, Trish believes she is going to meet a prince.

13.title: Burdens & Boynado
13.plot: When Trish's boy-band client "Boynado" threatens to split up, she searches to find a way to fix their problems. Meanwhile, Austin and Ally try to help a former impersonator find his own voice.

14.title: Bad Seeds & Bad Dates
14.plot: Ally learns that the new woman her Dad is seeing also happens to be the mom of a very difficult student at the A&A Music Factory.

15.title: Scary Spirits & Spooky Stories
15.plot: While visiting New York the group attends the Central Park Spooktacular, and it inspires them to tell their own scary stories.

16.title: Rejection & Rocketships
16.plot: When Ally is rejected from college, she decides to let go of her "perfect student" ways. Meanwhile, Austin and Dez discover their favorite childhood ride will shut down forever.

17.title: Cap and Gown & Can't Be Found
17.plot: When a missing library book threatens to keep Ally from graduating, Austin tries to find it. Meanwhile, Trish fakes some memorable moments in an attempt to get more photos in the yearbook.

18.title: Santas & Surprises
18.plot: One of Austin and Ally's music students is upset about spending Christmas away from her father, so the gang does everything they can to try and make her happy and realize that they're her family too.

19.title: Musicals & Moving On
19.plot: As the rest of the group prepares for the next phase of their lives, Trish is still determining what her next steps will be.

20.title: Duets & Destiny
20.plot: Years after the gang has gone their separate ways, Ally, Austin, Trish and Dez meet-up and learn what they have all been up to, individually.

1.title: Rockers & Writers
1.plot: Extroverted fun-loving Austin Moon becomes an overnight teen pop-singing sensation with a music video of a song he sub-consciously "borrowed" from a brilliant but shy and nerdy songwriter named Ally Dawson, who works at a local music store that's his favorite hangout. Realizing she's the key to his success, he tries to convince her to be his main songwriting partner. Together with the help of their respective best friends, aspiring film director Dez and the semi-employed Trish, they are determined to bring his performances and her songs to the top of the charts.

2.title: Kangaroos & Chaos
2.plot: Ally scribbles down Austin's song lyrics in illegible handwriting prompting Dez and Trish to start gathering strange props for the music video which they think correspond to her lyrics. After the odd collection of musical items begins arriving, they quickly work together to resolve the mix-up.

3.title: Secrets & Songbooks
3.plot: Ally loses her song writing book, which is also her top secret diary, so she and Trish comb the mall looking for her it, not knowing that Austin and Dez have already found it and read it, revealing that Ally has a secret crush. When Austin is convinced it's him, he tries to find a way to let Ally know they're just friends.

4.title: Zaliens & Cloud Watchers
4.plot: When Austin listens to the song Ally wrote that she thinks its about Austin, he hates it. Before he was going to sing the song he tells her that he doesn't like it. After that, they decided to hang out to find out what they like which doesn't go out well. Meanwhile, Dez and Trish has just realized that they have something in common.

5.title: Bloggers & Butterflies
5.plot: A mysterious blogger sets up a website designed to make Austin look bad, even though the real target of this person's hostility is Ally.

6.title: Tickets & Trashbags
6.plot: Austin is torn when he gets a gig at the Miami Music Internet Awards, but can only bring one guest.

7.title: Managers & Meatballs
7.plot: Austin gets seduced by top music manager Demonica Dixon who wants to get rid of Ally as his songwriter, Trish as his manager, and Dez as his music video director, and bring in her own team, all with the promise that he'll get a chance to perform along Times Square on New Year's Eve.

8.title: Club Owners & Quinceaneras
8.plot: Trish's Quinceanera is used by Austin as the opportunity for potential gigs, and an opportunity for Ally to finally start dating Dallas.

9.title: Deejays & Demos
9.plot: Austin overhears Ally performing a song in her own spare time that he's so impressed with, that he plays it on a local radio show in order to give her the credit she deserves. However, the exposure proves to be more than Austin is able to handle, and more than Ally is willing to handle, when the DJ demands a duet with the two of them on a future broadcast. So Austin and his team must scramble to find a way around his songwriter's stage fright and hide her from the public.

10.title: World Records & Work Wreckers
10.plot: Ally accidentally hires her crush, Dallas, to work at Sonic Boom. When he turns out to be a horrible employee, Ally hesitates to fire him, fearing it might ruin her chances of him liking her. Meanwhile, Austin and Dez compete to see who can spin a basketball on their finger the longest, granting them a spot in a world record book causing men to follow them around.

11.title: Songwriting & Starfish
11.plot: The gang tries to help Austin get ready for the Hot Summer Jam Contest on the beach, where he could win a chance to have his song played on the radio. Meanwhile, Ally tries to put her previous, unpleasant beach-going experiences behind her.

12.title: Soups & Stars
12.plot: Trish's new boss at Miss Suzy's Soups is also Ally's former elementary school teacher. When Ally inadvertently plays a prank on her, Miss Suzy's business starts to suffer. Ally feels terrible, so she, Austin, Trish and Dez come up with a plan to help get customers back into the doors by making a commercial.

13.title: Burglaries & Boobytraps
13.plot: A wave of burglaries has hit the Mall of Miami, but Ally thinks she has a foolproof plan to catch the thief. Due to footage from a security cam, the greed of Trish, and an overall rush to judgment, many of the other store owners suspect the thief may be Austin.

14.title: myTAB & My Pet
14.plot: While Team Austin takes turns waiting in line for the latest version of a popular computer tablet, Austin himself lets Ally's pet cockatiel escape while taking care of it.

15.title: Filmmaking & Fear Breaking
15.plot: Dez finally gets to make a short film and involves everybody from Team Austin. However the production exposes a phobia Austin has tried to hide.

16.title: Diners & Daters
16.plot: Trish gets a job at the Melody Diner, where Team Austin eats lunch, and Austin himself falls for one of the other waitresses.

17.title: Everglades & Ally-Gators
17.plot: Rapper Shiny Money invites Austin to stay at his houseboat in the Everglades, and against his better judgment the rest of Team Austin as well.

18.title: Successes & Setbacks
18.plot: A sudden medical mishap may derail Austin's efforts to impress a hot-shot music mogul.

19.title: Albums & Auditions
19.plot: Austin is finally on the verge of releasing his first album. However the celebrations may be short-lived as he and his friends help Ally get into the exclusive New York City music school she wanted to go to since she was 13, and he may end up losing his main songwriter for the first time.

1.title: Costumes & Courage
1.plot: The head of Austin's record company invites Team Austin to a Halloween Party at an allegedly haunted mansion, and gives him the opportunity to sing a duet with a famous female pop-country singer. But when Dez's new ghost-hunting obsession puts that singer temporarily out of commission, it forces Ally to do something she has been afraid to do for quite a while.

2.title: Backups & Breakups
2.plot: Team Austin tries to hire a backup dancer when one is injured during a publicity stunt. At the same time Ally begins to suspect that Trish and Dez have romantic secrets with each other, which turn out only to be partially true; Trish is found to be dating one of the dancers, and Dez secretly watches romantic movies. However, Ally discovers that the dancer's motives with both Trish and Austin are nowhere near as good as his skills on the dance floor.

3.title: Magazines & Made-Up Stuff
3.plot: Trish books Austin for the cover of a teeny-bopper magazine and makes up wild stories about his life outside of his music in order to impress them, forcing Austin to actually live up to the hype. It doesn't help that the magazine's top reporter is a ten year old girl who is just as much of a fan as she is a reporter.

4.title: Parents & Punishments
4.plot: Austin's parents put their feet down when his musical career affects his grades.

5.title: Crybabies & Cologne
5.plot: Trish's ex-boyfriend Trent tries to get back together with her. When this fails, he decides to steal the music and overall career of Team Austin.

6.title: Big Dreams & Big Apples
6.plot: Austin's dream of performing in Times Square on New Years Eve seems to be on the verge of coming true, but it has hit a few snags along the way, like Trish's bad cell phone app, and the general difficulty of getting around in New York City. Will a nanny named Jessie Prescott and crazed fan-girl Emma Ross be the solution to his problem?

7.title: Ferris Wheels & Funky Breath
7.plot: Austin and his friends shoot a music video for the song "No Ordinary Day" at a nearby carnival, thanks to Trish. But the gorgeous girl hired to play his girlfriend in the video has two strikes against her; 1)Chronic halitosis, and 2)She's Jimmy Starr's daughter.

8.title: Girlfriends & Girl Friends
8.plot: Austin's new video is a big hit, and Kira Starr has lost her halitosis, and won Austin's heart once again. While Ally tries to help him arrange the perfect date and convince Kira that they're not a couple, the effort to do so begins to kindle feelings about Austin she never thought she'd have.

9.title: Campers & Complications
9.plot: Ally's former summer camp crush visits her, causing Austin to feel jealous despite the fact that he is seeing Kira.

10.title: Chapters & Choices
10.plot: Ally's mother returns from the jungles of Africa to plug a book on her animal research, while she and Austin are continuing to consider their relationship beyond songwriting, and attempts to overcome her stage fright even as Kira pressures Austin on the status of their relationship.

11.title: Partners & Parachutes
11.plot: Still torn between his songwriter and his boss' daughter, Austin tries to convince Ally that she's the girl he wants, while simultaneously struggling to end his relationship with Kira without hurting her or his contract with Starr Records. Meanwhile, Ally's family and friends try to congratulate her for overcoming her stage fright in an elaborate way that doesn't necessarily go as planned.

12.title: Freaky Friends & Fan Fiction
12.plot: Dez enters a short story contest with a magic typewriter from an antique store Trish works at, and her boss is an enemy of his who steals it back causing all kinds of trouble for Team Austin.

13.title: Couples & Careers
13.plot: The pop-star and the songwriter are hired to write a song for an upcoming animated movie, and find that their newfound love life isn't having the best impact on their shared artistic ambitions. Meanwhile Dez and Trish have their own shared artistic ambitions to attend to when they make a homemade video for a contest related to their favorite horror/science fiction movie series.

14.title: Spas & Spices
14.plot: Trish gets a job at a spa and invites Ally to get some treatments. Meanwhile, Dez prepares to finally beat Chuck at the annual South Beach chili cook-off, and Austin picks up a valuable necklace for Ally while she's at the spa.

15.title: Solos & Stray Kitties
15.plot: Trish books a record deal for Ally which goes sour when she gets stuck as a member of a lame all-girl group.

16.title: Boy Songs & Badges
16.plot: Austin tries to write a song for himself instead of relying on Ally.

17.title: Tracks & Troubles
17.plot: Austin accidentally records over one of Kira's demos for her new album.

18.title: Viral Videos & Very Bad Dancing
18.plot: A local music magazine publisher and producer nominates Ally as one of five future artists to watch, until he notices her abysmal dancing skills.

19.title: Tunes & Trials
19.plot: Unable to buy a new song from Ally, former Stray Kitties manager Val Crawford sues Austin and his team over his latest hit. Dez and Trish, inspired by their favorite crime TV show, try to figure out who the girl in Austin's song is.

20.title: Future Sounds & Festival Songs
20.plot: A musical invention gives Austin a glimpse of the future that only looks bright.

21.title: Sports & Sprains
21.plot: Spirit Week at school prompts Austin to join the Varsity basketball team. Meanwhile, Dez and Chuck join the cheer squad, Trish pretends to care about school spirit to win money, and Ally does her first article for the school paper.

22.title: Beach Bums & Bling
22.plot: Austin helps out one of his old rock n roll heroes.

23.title: Family & Feuds
23.plot: On the verge of his sister Didi's 16th birthday, Dez is mortified to find his rival Chuck is her new boyfriend.

24.title: Moon Week & Mentors
24.plot: Austin and Ally are celebrity judges on a singing competition show.

25.title: Real Life & Reel Life
25.plot: Dez and Trish decide to making a movie about Austin and Ally's partnership.

26.title: Fresh Starts & Farewells
26.plot: Team Austin prepares to go with Austin as he embarks on his first tour.

1.title: Road Trips & Reunions
1.plot: Ally decides to fly out to catch one of Austin's performances.

2.title: What Ifs & Where's Austin
2.plot: Ally, Trish and Dez imagine life without Austin.

3.title: Presidents & Problems
3.plot: Following the last show of Austin's tour, the gang does some sight-seeing at a Washington D.C. museum, where Austin accidentally gets stuck with a priceless object and must find a way to return it before performing for the President

4.title: Beach Clubs & BFFs
4.plot: Ally starts hanging out with Kira Starr. Dez coaxes Austin into seeking buried treasure on the beach.

5.title: Mix-Ups & Mistletoes
5.plot: When Trish gets a prototype from the toy company of the Austin moon Doll, everything goes wrong when the doll does unexpected things.

6.title: Glee Clubs & Glory
6.plot: Austin and Ally compete against one another in a Glee Club competition.

7.title: Austin & Alias
7.plot: When Ally's record company refuses to let her write songs for Austin, she starts doing so under an assumed name.

8.title: Princesses & Prizes
8.plot: Austin agrees to be auctioned off on a date in order to help raise money for Ally's charity.

9.title: Cupids & Cuties
9.plot: Trish is nervous about an upcoming visit from a boy she has a crush on and does not act like herself when he takes her out on their first date. Meanwhile, Austin has to make a paper airplane for physics class.

10.title: Critics & Confidence
10.plot: Ally, Trish and Dez help relieve Austin from the slump he's fallen into after he receives his first negative review from a critic and is afraid to perform.

11.title: Directors & Divas
11.plot: Dez gets an unexpected opportunity to direct a movie that Austin is in, but things prove problematic when he has to work with Austin's co-star, Brandy Braxton, a high-maintenance actress.

12.title: Hunks & Homecoming
12.plot: Ally teams up with country hot shot Gavin to write a song, and they hit it off, making Austin jealous and fearing that the team is breaking up. Meanwhile, Dez and Chuck compete to make the best parade float for the cheer leading team.

13.title: Fashion Shows & First Impressions
13.plot: Austin must prove that he's not shallow to impress a girl he wants to take on a date.

14.title: Fanatics & Favors
14.plot: Austin, Ally and Trish learn that Dez has an unexpected relative who is coincidentally a huge Austin Moon fan, in addition to being an NBA superstar.

15.title: Eggs & Extraterrestrials
15.plot: When Dez, Trish and Austin convince Ally to attend the annual Zaliens Convention that's being held in Miami, Trish and Dez happen to stumble upon real Zaliens and the foursome must devise a plan to survive.

16.title: Proms & Promises
16.plot: Prom is all about the "Big Ask," so Austin asks Piper through a song while Ally patiently waits to see how Gavin will ask her.

17.title: Last Dances & Last Chances
17.plot: Austin realizes that he should be at prom with Ally, not Piper. After thinking he was telling Trish, he told Carrie. Now Austin needs to figure out what to do.

18.title: Videos & Villains
18.plot: Austin disappears before a performance because Brooke holds him captive until he writes a song for her, will he escape?

19.title: Beauties & Bullies
19.plot: Trish gets the lead role in the school play but she drops out when someone makes fun of her online.

20.title: Horror Stories & Halloween Scares
20.plot: Trapped in the store on Halloween, the gang tells scary stories.

21.title: Records & Wrecking Balls
21.plot: When Ally quits Sonic Boom to make more time for her music career, her father decides to sell the store. She and the rest of the gang have a hard time coming to terms with the fact that the store is soon going to be gone forever.

22.title: Relationships & Red Carpets
22.plot: Austin, Ally, Trish, and Dez all go to a premier. Austin and Ally's relationship develops, where Austin reveals his true feelings for Ally.

locations: Hollywood Center Studios - 1040 N. Las Palmas Avenue, Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA::(studio)
imdb.plot outline: A comedy about the unique relationship between a young songwriter, Ally Dawson, and Austin Moon, the overnight internet sensation who gains sudden notoriety after performing one of Ally's songs. Austin and Ally struggle with how to maintain and capitalize on Austin's newfound fame. Austin is more of a rebel type who doesn't follow the rules and is somewhat immature for his age, while Ally is conservative yet self-conscious.
imdb.title: Austin & Ally
plot: Following the lives of Austin, an aspiring confident musician, Ally, a quiet talented songwriter and their two friends.::Anonymous

A songwriter, Ally Dawson, works at a music store called Sonic Boom. One day, she meets a boy named Austin Moon. Austin steals a song from Ally and becomes an overnight sensation. Later, Ally forgives Austin and and they become partners with the help of Ally the shy songwriter and Austin the spotlight star.::Anonymous

A shy songwriter, Ally Dawson, works at her dad's music store "Sonic Boom." One day, she meets a boy named Austin Moon who loves the spotlight. Later, Ally finds out that Austin stole her song and tries to teach Austin a lesson but remotely failed. Ally decides to give him one more chance and they become partners. They couldn't have done it without the help of their friends Dez and Trish.::donahuehannah
